        "action": "Abolish ability grouping in all primary schools",
        "additional_details": "A study conducted by the OECD concluded: \u201ccountries which stream pupils into ability groups at an early age tend to have lower levels of achievement\". We want better education for our children in Britain.\r\n \r\nBeatriz Pont, an education analyst and one of the authors of the OECD's study, said \"streaming by ability at an early age \"fuelled a vicious cycle\" in which teachers had low expectations of students in the lowest sets. These students were often \"locked into a lower educational environment before they had a chance to develop \u2026 their potential.\u201d\r\nTo view the study: http://www.oecd.org/education/school/equityandqualityineducation-supportingdisadvantagedstudentsandschools.htm",
        "background": "Ability grouping is practiced across English primary education. \r\nA study conducted by the OECD concluded: \u201ccountries which stream pupils into ability groups at an early age tend to have lower levels of achievement\". We want better education for our children in Britain.",
